54b5497afb42861cc596595e36e4","tid":1833211,"uid":288670,"like":9,"dislike":0,"score":9,"quote":{"pid":"482ac92c89cdaf37b121d004be63546202c674cb","tid":1833211,"uid":270889,"like":10,"dislike":0,"score":10,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-01-21T17:45:24.000Z","msg":"俄羅斯電視台 <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/clown.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><br />\n此post已完"},"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-01-21T18:07:08.000Z","msg":"五毛狗沙田you開post 都唔洗睇啦<img src=\"/assets/faces/dog/haha.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-01-21T18:42:38.000Z","msg":"thx 又block一件"},{"pid":"57650f433ebc6a23eb3a4fe52fae6ff62533db45","tid":1833211,"uid":258345,"like":2,"dislike":1,"score":1,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-01-21T18:54:55.000Z","msg":"RT 係 俄版 人民日報 CCTV"},{"pid":"700759c6971b1cfa9951acbee7683aef920e3c3f","tid":1833211,"uid":260740,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"228b0f45fa1255e63731087d7c1b9e91e6e69f78","tid":1833211,"uid":133680,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-01-21T17:24:53.000Z","msg":"<a href=\"https://www.google.com/amp/s/www.rt.com/news/474756-hong-kong-protests-china-us/amp/\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Famp%2Fs%2Fwww.rt.com%2Fnews%2F474756-hong-kong-protests-china-us%2Famp%2F&d=fvWYig%2FFXUG8IHhaG2JvmIT2PPn%2Ft%2FQrHStoP3Eljfw%3D&h=6cc7977c\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://www.google.com/amp/s/www.rt.com/news/474756-hong-kong-protests-china-us/amp/</a><br />\n<br />\n.RTQUESTION MORELIVE<br />\nHomeWorld News<br />\nHong Kong unmasked: The real reasons &amp; instigators behind anti-Beijing riots<br />\n1 Dec, 2019 01:48 / Updated 2 months ago<br />\nRT<br />\n<br />\nAs Hong Kong&rsquo;s anti-government movement continues to rage, RT looks into what sparked the unrest, the dire social inequality problems that fuel it, and how forces in Washington exploited this public discontent for their own ends.<br />\nHaving personally witnessed brutal clashes and spoken to key figures on both sides of the barricades, RT America&rsquo;s Michele Greenstein paints a comprehensive picture of the protest&rsquo;s origins and handlers.<br />\n<br />\nThe contentious extradition bill, which was the catalyst for the uprising this summer, served only as a pretext, while its nature was grossly misinterpreted. It doesn&rsquo;t mean that the islanders &ndash; suffocated by prosaic issues like high prices, poor housing conditions, and declining employment prospects for graduates, rather than a lack of &lsquo;democracy&rsquo; &ndash; have nothing to be angry about.<br />\n<br />\nALSO ON <a href=\"http://RT.COM\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=http%3A%2F%2FRT.COM&d=fvWYig%2FFXUG8IHhaG2JvmIT2PPn%2Ft%2FQrHStoP3Eljfw%3D&h=adcdd9b0\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">RT.COM</a><br />\nHong Kong police secure THOUSANDS of PETROL BOMBS, GAS CANISTERS &amp; CHEMICALS as PolyU campus standoff ends<br />\nYet the demonstrators never challenged Hong Kong&rsquo;s own authorities over this social inequality, directing their rage solely at mainland China &ndash; all while destroying their own city and virtually begging the US to sanction it, just to hurt Beijing.<br />\n<br />\nWith young and progressive leaders of the Hong Kong uprising cheered as noble &lsquo;pro-democracy&rsquo; warriors and welcomed in the US with open arms, Washington isn&rsquo;t even trying to hide the fact that the protests have been hijacked to demonize and destabilize its main economic rival &ndash; China.<br />\n<br />\nALSO ON <a href=\"http://RT.COM\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=http%3A%2F%2FRT.COM&d=fvWYig%2FFXUG8IHhaG2JvmIT2PPn%2Ft%2FQrHStoP3Eljfw%3D&h=adcdd9b0\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">RT.COM</a><br />\nUS to launch new media network to provide Chinese diaspora with &lsquo;alternative&rsquo; news &ndash; report<br />\nMan set on fire by Hong Kong protesters &lsquo;can&rsquo;t recognize his own daughter&rsquo; after 10+ days in coma<br />\nHong Kong protesters hurl PETROL BOMBS at volunteers trying to clear roadblocks and shoot ARROWS at police<br />\nCatapulting Hong Kong into democracy? Media glorifies ANARCHY &amp; &lsquo;novel, defensive&rsquo; anti-police weapons of protesters<br />\n&ldquo;The original movement has been eroded. Now it&rsquo;s just about opposition to Chinese government and the subversion of state power,&rdquo; says Stanley Ng Chau-pei, president of the Federation of Trade Unions, the largest labor and political group in Hong Kong.<br />\n<br />\nIt&rsquo;s a &lsquo;color revolution&rsquo;<br />\n<br />\nWATCH the full reports by RT America&rsquo;s Michele Greenstein:<br />\n<br />\n<br />\nSubscribe to RT newsletter to get stories the mainstream media won&rsquo;t tell you.<br />\n<br />\nRT"},"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-01-21T20:36:32.000Z","msg":"出名製造假新聞既國家<img src=\"/assets/faces/dog/smile.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"df899644b0a5c97a47b79169f3a8d75306c62dc4","tid":1833211,"uid":133680,"like":0,"dislike":1,"score":-1,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-01-21T21:28:17.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/angel.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"06df6b26afeddb0b17b3fe13c5ac2d4d2276df9a","tid":1833211,"uid":269202,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-01-21T23:46:59.000Z","msg":"傻仔，錢都是我在美國轉過來，不信我立即轉一百萬落香港給你看"},{"pid":"7b8ca03ffadbcd2ddde169f404aaa788eb9f6aa5","tid":1833211,"uid":133680,"like":0,"dislike":1,"score":-1,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-01-22T00:20:16.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/angel.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"5a28867c7598357a7344515aae7a278f0664b32e","tid":1833211,"uid":75232,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-01-22T00:25:10.000Z","msg":"RT=Russian Times<br />\n<br />\npull"},{"pid":"e4cb317dca95e91e145d06e4faacc98d01257894","tid":1833211,"uid":169074,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-02-05T01:25:52.000Z","msg":"此回覆已被刪除"},{"pid":"93698807f88143262f2fdfb5fe5d8fc6b5e676d1","tid":